{"id":1580,"date":"2011-08-10T06:04:11","date_gmt":"2011-08-10T11:04:11","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/three_cheers_for_the_laundry_detergent.php"},"modified":"2011-08-10T06:04:11","modified_gmt":"2011-08-10T11:04:11","slug":"three_cheers_for_the_laundry_detergent","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/three_cheers_for_the_laundry_detergent.php","title":{"rendered":"Three Cheers for the Laundry Detergent"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cheer_threedux_logo.gif\" alt=\"Cheer Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Since 2006 when we launched Brand New there has been one constant: every two years, the Procter &amp; Gamble laundry detergent, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cheer.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Cheer<\/a>, redesigns. The first redesign came in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/hip_hip_boo.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">2007<\/a> and the second in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cheerier_cheer.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">2009<\/a>. We&#8217;ve become, like, their official identity biographers. Back in July, Cheer introduced its third look in four years.<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cheer_threedux_packaging.jpg\" alt=\"Cheer\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cheer_threedux_drop.gif\" alt=\"Cheer\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cheer_threedux_logos_old.gif\" alt=\"Cheer\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cheer_threedux_packaging_old.jpg\" alt=\"Cheer\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Pre-2007, 2007, and 2009 logo and bottles.<\/p>\n<p>This is the best of all attempts. Of the logos this is the least annoying compared to 2007&#8217;s squat version and 2009&#8217;s party-in-a-box version. 2011 is far from great &mdash; the rounded corners on the bottom of the characters are uncalled for and even though I get that they were going for tight letter spacing this seems a tad too tight for the product it represents &mdash; but it&#8217;s an improvement. The bottle is actually pleasant and kind of cool. The dark blue bottle is somewhat badass and the color drop contrasts really well. Someone was even paying enough attention to align the &#8220;h&#8221; in the logo and the text description below it with the third column of the color grid. It&#8217;s not a groundbreaking gesture, but based on previous executions this is the M&uuml;ller-Brockmann of Cheer packaging.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to Diane Van Leunen for the tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110810_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110810_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110810_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110810_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_start.gif\" alt=\"Voting Begins\" \/>\n<table class=\"table\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n\t<tr valign=\"top\">\n        <!--VOTE CONCEPT-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_col\">\n\t\t